"n.兇恶的老妇，老巫婆 【英】 n. 兇恶的老妇，老巫婆( a nasty, bad-tempered woman) 【记】 原意为'骑坏的老马', hard－ridden→harri dan n. 刻薄恶毒的老妇人; 老巫婆 【记】原指难骑的老马hard ride, 后引申为老巫婆harri = hurry, dan蛋: 再不hurry就被老巫婆变成蛋了. 【记】音：骇人旦，骇人，吓人的老旦(旦在京剧中指女演员，花旦，老旦)；hairy + dan 旦→多毛，长发的女人→老巫婆；horror 恐惧 + dan 旦, 吓人的老旦 【相关】harry(harass) 不断骚扰，折磨 harridan (n.)  1700, ""one that is half Whore, half Bawd"" [""Dictionary of the Canting Crew""]; ""a decayed strumpet"" [Johnson], probably from French haridelle ""a poore tit, or leane ill-favored jade,"" [Cotgrave, 1611], in French from 16c., of unknown origin."
